did.abstract:
Collection includes letterpress books containing political,
        personal and business correspondence; financial records from most of his businesses;
        personal, political and business correspondence;, political and personal scrapbooks;
        clippings; and miscellaneous other material.

note.p:
Political and history 1904-1911; Chattert and Warren feud 1905; Investigation of
                  Warren for fraud 1905; Shoshone Reservation and irrigation; Wool growers and sheep
                  industry; Wool Tariff 1909; Wyoming's Resources; Enlargement of Fort Russell;
                  Warren's visit to Philippines and Japan 1905; Election of 1906, 1908, 1910;
                  Frontier Days Celebrations 1906, 1907, 1908, 1910, good pictures and history; Taft
                  visits Cheyenne; Roosevelt visits Cheyenne 1910; Battleship "Wyoming";
                  Carey-Warren split 1910; Van DeVanter named associate justice 1910; Building of
                  Plains Hotel; Warren Chairman of Senate Appropriation Committee 1910; microfilm
                  reel 154

Personal 1910-1914; Warren Chairman of Senate Appropriation Committee 1911;
                  Plains Hotel; Marriage of Clara Morgan 1911; miscellaneous criticisms; Pershing in
                  Philippines; 1913 Tariff and wool; microfilm reel 158

Politics and history 1928-1929; Election of 1928; Burlington Depot for Cheyenne;
                  Hoover visits Cheyenne; Frontier Days 1928; Johnson County War and early history;
                  Teton National Park; Washakie and Grace R. Hebard; Death of Warren and his
                  successor; microfilm reel 159

Personal 1914-1918; The Washington scene; Woman suffrage; Death of Mrs. Pershing;
                  Miscellaneous national events; Pershing in Mexico; Intention to retire in 1919;
                  Pershing and World War I; Warren enters 1918 campaign; microfilm reel 160

Politics 1897-1899; Cheyenne City politics; Laramie County politics; Elections
                  1898-1899; Miscellaneous Senatorial activities; Frontier Days-August 1899;
                  microfilm reel 162
